        <h1>Timers Memory Leak</h1>
        <div class="description">
            <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> A timers leak occurs when timers (setInterval, setTimeout) are not properly cleared. These timers keep references to their callback functions and any variables used within those functions, preventing garbage collection.</p>
            <p><strong>Example Code:</strong></p>
            <pre>
function startTimer() {
    setInterval(() => {
        console.log('Timer leak');
        // Simulate significant memory usage
        const leakArray = new Array(100000).fill('leak');
    }, 100); // Timer that is never cleared, running more frequently
}
            </pre>
